OL,3,CSolong container ship that crashed in
OL,4,CNorth Sea arrives in Aberdeen
OL,6,FA container ship that hit a US tanker
OL,7,Fin the North Sea, leading to its
OL,8,Fcaptain being charged with
OL,9,Fmanslaughter, has arrived in Aberdeen.
OL,11,FPortuguese vessel Solong was towed to
OL,12,Fthe Scottish port city for "safe
OL,13,Fberthing" after it crashed into the
OL,14,Fanchored tanker Stena Immaculate off
OL,15,Fthe East Yorkshire coast on March 10.
OL,17,FRescuers saved 36 people from both
OL,18,Fships, with one 38-year-old sailor
OL,19,Ffrom the Solong, named Filipino
OL,20,Fnational Mark Angelo Pernia, missing
OL,21,Fand presumed dead.
