OL,3,CSolong container ship that crashed in
OL,4,CNorth Sea arrives in Aberdeen
OL,6,FThe Solong was still burning a week
OL,7,Fafter it collided with the US fuel
OL,8,Ftanker, whose crew were praised as
OL,9,F"heroic" for triggering a crucial fire-
OL,10,Ffighting system before abandoning ship.
OL,12,FCrowley, the maritime company managing
OL,13,Fthe ship, said that thanks to their
OL,14,Fefforts, only one of the Stena
OL,15,FImmaculate's cargo tanks containing
OL,16,Fjet fuel was damaged.
OL,18,FChief coastguard Paddy O'Callaghan
OL,19,Fsaid: "Salvage of the Solong has
OL,20,Fprogressed to enable its relocation to
OL,21,Fthe Port of Aberdeen for safe berthing.
