OL,3,CSolong container ship that crashed in
OL,4,CNorth Sea arrives in Aberdeen
OL,6,FFollowing the collision, thousands of
OL,7,Fplastic pellets used in plastics
OL,8,Fproduction, known as nurdles, were
OL,9,Freleased from ruptured containers on
OL,10,Fthe Solong and began washing up on
OL,11,Fbeaches on the Norfolk coast, where a
OL,12,Fclean-up operation is continuing.
OL,14,FAccording to conservationists, the
OL,15,Fnurdles are not toxic but can harm
OL,16,Fanimals if ingested.
